Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.65,0:00:17.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我很高兴借这次机会，Mark Shuttleworth 到中国来的机会，为大家做一个现场演讲
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.74,0:00:24.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Mark Shuttleworth 是 Ubuntu 的创始人，可能大家已经听说过他的大名了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.30,0:00:31.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,去年在北航我们曾经做过一次这样的演讲，当时现场反应也比较热烈
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.37,0:00:37.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以这回 Mark 来中国的时候我们就安排了这次是在上海
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.00,0:00:43.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为已经在北京做过了，这也是一次难得的机会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.14,0:00:54.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我就不多说了，下面有请 Mark Shuttleworth 为大家讲述他自己的经历和有关开源软件的一些概念和故事，谢谢
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.82,0:01:02.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大家下午好。来到这里真是太好了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.82,0:01:02.45,English,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon everybody. It's wonderful to be here
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.41,0:01:07.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Amy 告诉我，你们都是不同专业的学生
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.41,0:01:07.75,English,,0,0,0,,Amy tells me that you would all be students of a whole bunch of different things
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.75,0:01:12.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在我开始演讲之前，我想知道有关你们的一些情况
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.75,0:01:12.48,English,,0,0,0,,and I'm keen to know a little bit about you before I start at speaking
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.48,0:01:16.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以你们能不能告诉我你们在学习什么专业？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.48,0:01:16.96,English,,0,0,0,,so could you give me some indication of what you guys are studying
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.01,0:01:19.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里有多少人在学习商科？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.01,0:01:19.02,English,,0,0,0,,How many guys here are studying business
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.72,0:01:20.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在大学中学习商科
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.72,0:01:20.77,English,,0,0,0,,here at university
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.80,0:01:25.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,工程专业？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.80,0:01:25.82,English,,0,0,0,,Engineer?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.51,0:01:28.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,计算机工程？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.51,0:01:28.11,English,,0,0,0,,Computer engineering
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.03,0:01:31.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你们中的大多数人都在学习计算机工程
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.03,0:01:31.53,English,,0,0,0,,majority of you are studying computer engineering
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.81,0:01:34.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你们当中有多少人愿意自己创业？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.81,0:01:34.97,English,,0,0,0,,How many of you will prefer to start your own businesses
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.97,0:01:38.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,又有多少人愿意在大公司工作？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.97,0:01:38.02,English,,0,0,0,,and how many would prefer to start working in large company?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.69,0:01:41.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么，有多少人愿意在大公司开始工作？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.69,0:01:41.22,English,,0,0,0,,So how many would prefer to start working in a large company
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.07,0:01:45.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,又有多少人想自己创业？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.07,0:01:45.37,English,,0,0,0,,and how many of you want to start your own businesses
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.79,0:01:50.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我可以告诉你，在这群人中，谁会成为真正的富人
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.79,0:01:50.46,English,,0,0,0,,I can tell you who's gonna be really wealthy out of the crowd
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.46,0:01:53.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是那些举手说要自己创业的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.46,0:01:53.79,English,,0,0,0,,the people who put up their hands up to say they're gonna start their own businesses
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.02,0:02:01.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我今天想简单谈谈创业，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.02,0:02:01.51,English,,0,0,0,,What I thought I would talk about today is entrepreneurship because
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.58,0:02:06.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我相信经济变革与技术变革同样重要
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.58,0:02:06.20,English,,0,0,0,,I believe that economical change is just as important as technological change
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.20,0:02:09.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而技术变革与社会变革同样重要。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.20,0:02:09.14,English,,0,0,0,,which is just as important as social change
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.16,0:02:13.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而真正推动经济变革的是创业者
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.16,0:02:13.53,English,,0,0,0,,And it's entrepreneurs who really drive economical change
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.53,0:02:17.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是企业家有效地利用新的想法，把它们变成新的企业
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.53,0:02:17.78,English,,0,0,0,,It's entrepreneurs who effectively take new ideas, turn them into new businesses
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.78,0:02:20.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并把它们变成全球现象。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.78,0:02:20.25,English,,0,0,0,, and turn them into global phenomenons
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.62,0:02:24.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我相信，这个国家将会产生出
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.62,0:02:24.08,English,,0,0,0,,And I'm convinced that this is a country which is gonna produce
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.21,0:02:27.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,许多下一代的伟大企业家
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.21,0:02:27.78,English,,0,0,0,,Many of the next generation of great entrepreneurs
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.78,0:02:31.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，我觉得这会是一个有趣的话题
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.78,0:02:31.80,English,,0,0,0,,So I feel that that would be an interesting thing to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.80,0:02:37.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我要求你列出一些在过去10年中创办的伟大企业
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.80,0:02:37.99,English,,0,0,0,,If I ask you to list some great businesses that have been started in the last
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.42,0:02:42.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哪些公司，哪些名字是你会想到的？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.42,0:02:42.73,English,,0,0,0,,In the last 10 years. What companies, what names would you throw out
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.84,0:02:46.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有人想发言吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.84,0:02:46.68,English,,0,0,0,,Who wants to suggest?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.65,0:02:51.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是个不错的选择。谷歌是一家在过去10年中创办的伟大企业。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.65,0:02:51.04,English,,0,0,0,,It's a great choice. Google is a great business started in the last 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.14,0:02:55.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,苹果公司。苹果是一个伟大的企业。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.14,0:02:55.51,English,,0,0,0,,Apple. Apple is a great business.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.51,0:03:01.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们在过去10年里发生了根本性的变化。他们已经从根本上改变了人们对苹果的看法
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.51,0:03:01.75,English,,0,0,0,,They've radically changed in the last 10 years. They've radically changed the way people think about Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.75,0:03:06.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,10年前，也许每个人都认为苹果已经完了，而今天他们成为了所有人的宠儿
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.75,0:03:06.33,English,,0,0,0,,10 years ago maybe everybody thought Apple was dying and today they're the darling
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.33,0:03:11.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们正在引领潮流。这是一个非常有趣的例子
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.33,0:03:11.47,English,,0,0,0,,They're setting the trend. It was a very interesting example
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.48,0:03:13.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有哪些你欣赏的公司？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.48,0:03:13.42,English,,0,0,0,,What are the other companies you admire?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.42,0:03:20.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,(听不清)另一家伟大的公司。但它不是一个新的公司，它没有真正改变事情
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.42,0:03:20.40,English,,0,0,0,,(inaudible) Another great company. But it's not a new company it's not really changing things
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.71,0:03:29.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其他的呢？还有哪些公司是你们欣赏的？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.71,0:03:29.82,English,,0,0,0,,Other brands, tell me about the company you admire
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.82,0:03:33.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,NetApp。我没听说过它
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.82,0:03:33.74,English,,0,0,0,,NetApp. I don't know that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.97,0:03:39.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Network Appliance。NetApp。OK 这很有意思
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.97,0:03:39.47,English,,0,0,0,,Network Appliance. NetApp. OK That's very interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.65,0:03:48.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实上，近乎定义了我们这个时代的公司，是像Ebay和Google这样的。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.65,0:03:48.65,English,,0,0,0,,The fact that the businesses that are kinda defining our age are companies like ebay and Google
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.77,0:03:51.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,中国版的Ebay是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.77,0:03:51.37,English,,0,0,0,,What's the Chinese equivalent of ebay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.42,0:03:57.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,（它们拥有）全新的技术带来的优势，而这些技术在10年前根本就不存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.42,0:03:57.48,English,,0,0,0,,Advantage of completely new technologies that didn't really exist 10 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.48,0:03:59.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们都是
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.48,0:03:59.15,English,,0,0,0,,They are all companies that effectively
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.15,0:04:04.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们今天都大名鼎鼎，作为伟大的公司被我们所接受。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.15,0:04:04.12,English,,0,0,0,,We all have them as brand names today and we accept them today as great companies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.12,0:04:07.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但在10年前，你甚至无法想象这样的公司能够存在。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.12,0:04:07.62,English,,0,0,0,,But 10 years ago you couldn't even dream that a company like that could exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.15,0:04:13.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你想象一下过去10年中在科技领域所创造的财富
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.15,0:04:13.25,English,,0,0,0,,If you look at the wealth that's been created in technology over the last 10 years
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.31,0:04:19.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们大多数都是利用在1995年还不存在的技术创造的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.31,0:04:19.23,English,,0,0,0,,It's largely being created using technology that just didn't exist in 1995
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.23,0:04:25.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并围绕着1995年还不存在的社群和客户群体而建立。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.23,0:04:25.20,English,,0,0,0,,and built around communities and customer bases just didn't exist in 1995
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.20,0:04:31.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这突出了我认为也许是伟大的企业家最重要的特征
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.20,0:04:31.77,English,,0,0,0,,That highlights what I think perhaps is the most important characteristics of great entrepreneurs
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.77,0:04:36.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他/她们了解变化。他/她们了解这个世界正在如何变化
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.77,0:04:36.48,English,,0,0,0,,is that they understand change. They understand how the world is changing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.71,0:04:39.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且他/她们非常希望自己能够推动其中一部分的变化
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.71,0:04:39.94,English,,0,0,0,,And they very much want to be part of that change
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.52,0:04:47.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我认为，如果你作为一个企业家，如果你想成为一个伟大的企业家
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.52,0:04:47.71,English,,0,0,0,,I think if you as an entrepreneur if you want to be a great entrepreneur
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.82,0:04:49.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么你就必须了解
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.82,0:04:49.83,English,,0,0,0,,Then you have to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.85,0:04:52.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,世界是如何变化的，你必须了解
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.85,0:04:52.14,English,,0,0,0,,How the world is changing, you have to understand how
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.18,0:04:55.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,世界上正在发生的变化将如何影响你的国家
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.18,0:04:55.23,English,,0,0,0,,Changes that are going on in the world are going to affect your country
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.23,0:05:02.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个国家就经历了巨大的变化。如果你回想起10年前，你觉得这里都发生了哪些变化？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.23,0:05:02.45,English,,0,0,0,,This is a country of great change. If you look back 10 years, how would you say things have changed here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.45,0:05:10.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你认为今天正在进行的变化的关键因素有哪些？互联网
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.45,0:05:10.30,English,,0,0,0,,What would you say are the key element of change that's going on today? The Internet
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.30,0:05:14.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你是否认为自己与外部世界有非常紧密的联系，你是否觉得
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.30,0:05:14.86,English,,0,0,0,,You feel very connected to the outside world, you feel like
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.86,0:05:18.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你可以关注新闻，你可以了解全球的技术发展？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.86,0:05:18.70,English,,0,0,0,,you can follow the news, that you can follow technology developments globally?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.86,0:05:27.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我认为你可以。我认为你可以坐在这里的大学里，并且同时清楚地知道化学领域发生了什么
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.86,0:05:27.01,English,,0,0,0,,I think you can. I think you can sit here in university and you can know exactly what's going on in chemistry
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.01,0:05:31.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你可以确切地知道物理学中发生了什么，你可以确切地知道计算机科学和商业中又发生了什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.01,0:05:31.85,English,,0,0,0,,you can exactly what's going on in physics, you can learn exactly what's going on in computer science, in business
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.86,0:05:35.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这很棒。我们是能实现这些的第一代人。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.86,0:05:35.58,English,,0,0,0,,That's amazing. We're the first generation to be able to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.58,0:05:39.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对于我们父母那一代人，世界上一个地方的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.58,0:05:39.72,English,,0,0,0,,Our parents' generation, it took a very long time before an idea
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.72,0:05:41.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要经历很长时间才能传到世界上的另一个地方。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.72,0:05:41.85,English,,0,0,0,,from one part of the world reached somewhere else in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.85,0:05:48.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以这是最大的变化。我预测，中国在未来的一代……
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.85,0:05:48.51,English,,0,0,0,,So this is the biggest change. I would predict, that over the next generation, china is going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.51,0:05:54.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你们创业时的世界将变得和非洲完全一样
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.51,0:05:54.11,English,,0,0,0,,The world in which you do business is going to become exactly like Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.11,0:05:58.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,与欧洲，与美国完全一样。换言之，你将能够
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.11,0:05:58.88,English,,0,0,0,,exactly like Europe, exactly like America, in the sense that you will be able to to to to to participate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.88,0:06:06.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,作为一等公民随时参与到你们想要参与的任何事业中
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.88,0:06:06.82,English,,0,0,0,,as first class citizens instantly in whatever busines sit is that you choose to participate in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.90,0:06:08.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.90,0:06:08.06,English,,0,0,0,,Okay
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.16,0:06:11.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么，伟大的企业家都具有什么特点？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.16,0:06:11.92,English,,0,0,0,,So what are the characteristics of great entrepreneurs?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.92,0:06:16.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你们认为，成为一个伟大的企业家需要什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.92,0:06:16.56,English,,0,0,0,,Does anybody want to suggest, what does it take to be a great entrepreneur?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.61,0:06:26.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,激情。我想说这是最重要的特点。如果你想做出点什么，如果你想创立一些东西
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.61,0:06:26.60,English,,0,0,0,,Passion. I would say that's the number one characteristic. If you want to create well, if you want to build something
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.61,0:06:31.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你就必须全身心地投入，完全地将自己投入其中。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.61,0:06:31.54,English,,0,0,0,,you are going to have to devote yourself to it, you have to devote yourself to it completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.54,0:06:36.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而这实际上是相当困难的。有很多不同的诱惑。（比如）你能很容易找到一份高薪的工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.54,0:06:36.61,English,,0,0,0,,And that's actually quite difficult. Different distractions. It is easy to get a job that pays you good salaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.61,0:06:42.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在今天，想要过上普通人的生活是很容易的。但是，如果你想过更好的生活
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.61,0:06:42.01,English,,0,0,0,,It's easy to to live an average life today. But if you want to live an exceptional life
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.01,0:06:45.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你就必须完全地致力于一个想法。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.01,0:06:45.97,English,,0,0,0,,you have to be totally totally committed to an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.97,0:06:50.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果这是一个令你真正着迷的想法，你就能更轻松地致力于其中。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.97,0:06:50.68,English,,0,0,0,,And it's much easier to be committed to that idea, if you actually really fascinated by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.68,0:06:53.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以我要告诉你的第一件事是，如果你想创造财富
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.68,0:06:53.59,English,,0,0,0,,So the number one thing I will tell you is, if you want to create wealth
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.59,0:06:55.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你想成为非常富有的人，如果你想成为
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.59,0:06:55.72,English,,0,0,0,,if you want to become very wealthy, if you want to be
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.08,0:07:01.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,谷歌的创始人，或Ebay，NetApp，或者SalesForce.com的创始人那样的人，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.08,0:07:01.36,English,,0,0,0,,like the founders of Google, or the founder of ebay or the founder of NetApp, or the founder of SalesForce.com,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.96,0:07:05.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你需要拥有一个如此令你着迷的想法，以至于
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.96,0:07:05.80,English,,0,0,0,,You're going to have an idea that you find so fascinating that you're willing to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.80,0:07:11.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你愿意全身心地投入到这个想法中去，而不顾其他所有你面前的容易的机会
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.80,0:07:11.72,English,,0,0,0,,devote yourself to it to the exclusion of all of the other easy opportunities
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.72,0:07:17.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不是吗？我遇到过很多赚了几十上百亿的企业家们
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.72,0:07:17.72,English,,0,0,0,,that you face, right? I meet a lot of entrepreneurs, people who make billions and billions and billions of dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.37,0:07:24.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而他们中没有任何一个人对自己的工作不具有全部的热情
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.37,0:07:24.49,English,,0,0,0,,And I don't know any one of them who's not totally passionate about what they do
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.06,0:07:28.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而如果你，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.06,0:07:28.26,English,,0,0,0,,and if you, um.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.25,0:07:37.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你允许自己随大流变得平庸，如果你允许自己
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.25,0:07:37.01,English,,0,0,0,,If you allow yourself effectively to be drawn in to the average flow, if you allow yourself to be,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.01,0:07:42.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,被大公司定义来定义自己想要实现的目标
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.01,0:07:42.74,English,,0,0,0,,to define your objectives in terms of what the large company is telling you to do
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.74,0:07:46.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么你就很难对它充满激情；而如果你要去推动自己的变革
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.74,0:07:46.58,English,,0,0,0,,then it's hard to be so passionate about it, whereas if you say you are going to go out and drive that change
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.58,0:07:50.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么你将更容易地对这个目标充满激情。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.58,0:07:50.31,English,,0,0,0,,Then it's much easier to be really really passionate about.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.31,0:07:53.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你们认为企业家还有什么特点？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.31,0:07:53.31,English,,0,0,0,,What else can you say of entrepreneurs?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.31,0:07:57.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,创新。正是如此。创新都有关于变化
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.31,0:07:57.39,English,,0,0,0,,Innovation. Exactly. Innovation is all about change.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.74,0:08:01.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有两种成功的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.74,0:08:01.02,English,,0,0,0,,There are two ways to be successful
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.97,0:08:05.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,两种成功的方式，而我想最成功的人都或多或少两者兼具
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.97,0:08:05.86,English,,0,0,0,,Two ways to be successful, and I suppose the most successful people have a bit of both of this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.86,0:08:09.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但成功的第一种方式是极度的高效
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.86,0:08:09.21,English,,0,0,0,,but one way to be successful is to be extremely efficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.78,0:08:14.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不是吗？直面你要做的事情，并且非常非常高效地完成它们
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.78,0:08:14.38,English,,0,0,0,,Right? To take what you've been asked to do and to do it very, very efficiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.78,0:08:18.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你正在经营一家企业，你需要确保该企业是非常高效的，不是吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.78,0:08:18.54,English,,0,0,0,,Or if you're running a business to make sure that that business is very, very efficient, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.54,0:08:20.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,假设你正在经营一家航空公司。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.54,0:08:20.72,English,,0,0,0,,So say you're running an airline.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.72,0:08:24.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你能取得成功的第一个方法是，确保你经营的航空公司
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.72,0:08:24.58,English,,0,0,0,,But one way you can succeed at this airline is making sure that you run a more
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.58,0:08:27.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比你所有的其他竞争对手都更高效，对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.58,0:08:27.64,English,,0,0,0,,efficient airline than all of your other competitors, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.43,0:08:33.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以这有点像，你们在中国用Avis吗？那个租车公司，Avis？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.43,0:08:33.71,English,,0,0,0,,So that's a little bit like, do you have Avis in this country? The rental car company, Avis?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.57,0:08:38.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好吧，国际上有一家公司叫Avis，它的口号是，我们更努力。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.57,0:08:38.69,English,,0,0,0,,OK internationally there's a company called Avis, and its slogan is, we try harder.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.61,0:08:42.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,基本上，他们的意思是，我们做的事情和其他人一模一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.61,0:08:42.27,English,,0,0,0,,Basically, what they're saying is, we do exactly the same thing as everybody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.27,0:08:45.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们不做任何不同的事情，但我们更努力，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.27,0:08:45.05,English,,0,0,0,,We don't do anything differently, but we try harder, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.90,0:08:50.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在我遇到的大多数企业家，他们都不属于这个类别。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.90,0:08:50.14,English,,0,0,0,,Now most of the entrepreneurs that I meet, they don't fall into that category.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.14,0:08:54.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们不一定是最高效的管理者，或者说不一定
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.14,0:08:54.86,English,,0,0,0,,They're not necessarily extremely efficient managers, they're not necessarily extremely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.86,0:08:59.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,具有最强的业务能力，但他们所做的是，他们创新。他们改变事情。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.86,0:08:59.67,English,,0,0,0,,Operationly strong, but what they do is they innovate. They change things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.48,0:09:06.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我认为我这么多年来学到的可能是最大的教训，就是
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.48,0:09:06.19,English,,0,0,0,,Possibly the greatest lesson, I think that I've learned over the years is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.19,0:09:11.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不管你做什么，大多数正在发生的变化都发生在社会中。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.19,0:09:11.09,English,,0,0,0,,that most of the changes that are happening are changes that are happening in society, despite what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.09,0:09:12.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为它是一个如此巨大的全球经济。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.09,0:09:12.61,English,,0,0,0,,Because it's such a huge global economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.10,0:09:16.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然你仍然可以做出改变，可以创新
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.10,0:09:16.53,English,,0,0,0,,usually what's happening is that there is an underlying change going on in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.53,0:09:20.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但通常的情况是，社会正在潜移默化地改变。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.53,0:09:20.42,English,,0,0,0,,usually what's happening is that there is an underlying change going on in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.20,0:09:26.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，如果你了解这种潜在的变化，你清楚未来会如何变化
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.20,0:09:26.00,English,,0,0,0,,So if you understand that underlying change and you understand how the position is so forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.10,0:09:31.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么你就可以非常有效地驾驭这种变化的浪潮。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.10,0:09:31.26,English,,0,0,0,,Then you can effectively ride the wave of that change very efficiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.04,0:09:34.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来建立一种新的业务。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.04,0:09:34.89,English,,0,0,0,,To to build a new kind of business.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.89,0:09:37.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，虽然人们有时说企业家是创新者
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.89,0:09:37.84,English,,0,0,0,,So while people sometimes say that, you know, the entrepreneur is the innovator.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.04,0:09:43.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但多数时候，企业家不过是在理解社会上正在发生的变化。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.04,0:09:43.08,English,,0,0,0,,Usually what's happening is the entrepreneur is just understanding change that's going on in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.51,0:09:49.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，加入你在其他人之前就了解互联网是如何工作的，那么你就可以预测
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.51,0:09:49.19,English,,0,0,0,,So if you understand how the Internet works, for example, before everybody else does, then you can predict.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.43,0:09:54.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,互联网将会创造对新类型服务的需求。这样你就可以提前适应这个变化
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.43,0:09:54.99,English,,0,0,0,,That that will create demand for new kinds of services. And you can position yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.84,0:10:01.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来在其他人之前提供这些服务。所以说你实际上并没有“创造”互联网。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.84,0:10:01.40,English,,0,0,0,,To offer those services before everybody else does, so it's not as though you're actually creating the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.02,0:10:04.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个目标对于任何一个人或一个公司来说都太大了。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.02,0:10:04.91,English,,0,0,0,,That's too big for any one person or one company to do
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:10.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是，如果你了解互联网将如何改变你的社会和你身边的商业世界
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:10.15,English,,0,0,0,,But if you understand how the Internet is going to change your society and the business world around you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.15,0:10:13.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么你就可以适应这个变化，进而成为更有效的经营者。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.15,0:10:13.72,English,,0,0,0,,then you can position yourself to be the more efficient operator.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.72,0:10:21.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我认为这是一件更有趣的事情，对吧，驾驭着这些改变社会的浪潮。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.72,0:10:21.27,English,,0,0,0,,For me, that's a lot more fun, right, to ride these waves of change and through society.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.27,0:10:27.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在我的一生中，我们所看到的大变革的浪潮首先是在80年代初开始的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.27,0:10:27.07,English,,0,0,0,,So the big waves of change that we've seen in my lifetime have been first starting in the early 80s
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.07,0:10:30.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,全球化的变革浪潮
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.07,0:10:30.08,English,,0,0,0,,a wave of change towards globalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.08,0:10:35.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1980年，如果你在英国有一百万英镑，你没法
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.08,0:10:35.85,English,,0,0,0,,In 1980, if you had a million pounds in England, you weren't allowed to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.85,0:10:39.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把这一百万英镑带到其他地方去投资和经商。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.85,0:10:39.82,English,,0,0,0,,take that million pounds anywhere else to go and invest and create business.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.82,0:10:42.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这在今天几乎是难以想象的，因为上海是一个全球都市
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.82,0:10:42.82,English,,0,0,0,,It's almost crazy today, because Shanghai is a global capital, you have
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.82,0:10:48.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每周有数千亿英镑通过上海，对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.82,0:10:48.48,English,,0,0,0,,you have hundreds of billions of pounds coming through Shanghai every week, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.48,0:10:56.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但在27年前，这个行业并不存在，因为当时有非常严格的法规
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.48,0:10:56.16,English,,0,0,0,,But 27 years ago that didn't exist, that industry didn't exist because there were very strict rules about
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.16,0:10:59.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,禁止你在本国之外投资。而在上一代
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.16,0:10:59.17,English,,0,0,0,,not investing outside of your own country. And in the last generation
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.17,0:11:02.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几乎所有这些法规都被废除了，于是
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.17,0:11:02.72,English,,0,0,0,,basically all of those rules have have been swept away, so
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.27,0:11:05.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一些企业家发了大财，因为他/她们预见到了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.27,0:11:05.98,English,,0,0,0,,some entrepreneurs made huge fortunes because they foresee
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.98,0:11:10.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,全球化，或全球化的力量，将意味着
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.98,0:11:10.87,English,,0,0,0,,that globalization, or the forces of globalization, would mean that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.33,0:11:14.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,世界上任何地方的任何生产能力都应当
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.33,0:11:14.97,English,,0,0,0,,Any particular kind of capacity anywhere in the world should
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.54,0:11:20.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以同样的方式定价。如果你能以一个价格在英国生产一样商品，而在印度制造一些东西的价格只需要它的一半
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.54,0:11:20.19,English,,0,0,0,,ultimately be priced the same way that if you could manufacture something in the UK for one price
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.19,0:11:25.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么所有生产它的产能都会转移（去到印度）
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.19,0:11:25.58,English,,0,0,0,,to manufacture something in India for half that price, that all of that manufacturing capacity move.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.58,0:11:27.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，这是社会的一个巨大变化。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.58,0:11:27.86,English,,0,0,0,,So that's one huge change that went through society.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.93,0:11:33.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在我的一生中，社会的第二个巨大变化是互联网。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.93,0:11:33.45,English,,0,0,0,,The second huge change that surfed through society in my lifetime was the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.27,0:11:40.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这意味着信息可以在世界任何地方免费即时移动
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.27,0:11:40.38,English,,0,0,0,,It's effectively meant that information could move at no cost instantly anywhere in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.38,0:11:43.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,起初，能够自由移动的是资本。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.38,0:11:43.23,English,,0,0,0,,and at first it was capital that was able to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.99,0:11:47.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而贯穿社会的下一个重大变化是信息
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.99,0:11:47.52,English,,0,0,0,,The next big change that scrape through society was information
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.52,0:11:49.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使得信息也能够高效地移动，非常非常高效。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.52,0:11:49.63,English,,0,0,0,,making information effectively move very, very efficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.41,0:11:54.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在仍然有障碍和壁垒，还有防火墙和过滤器之类的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.41,0:11:54.53,English,,0,0,0,,And there are still blocks and barriers and firewalls and filtering and things like that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.53,0:11:58.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但趋势很明显是，信息将会在任何地方都能即时获得。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.53,0:11:58.57,English,,0,0,0,,but the trend absolutely is to make sure that information is instantly available anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.28,0:12:05.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人们最初想到的是分享信息的能力
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.28,0:12:05.20,English,,0,0,0,,And people initially thought about that in terms of the ability to send stuff out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.53,0:12:11.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是，如果你可以建立一个网站，现在你可以接触到世界上的每一个客户
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.53,0:12:11.64,English,,0,0,0,,But if you could set up a website, now you could reach every customer in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.64,0:12:14.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每一种技术都可以让你与全世界的客户进行沟通。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.64,0:12:14.01,English,,0,0,0,,every technology can connect to customer in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.27,0:12:17.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，下一个我们开始看到的大变化
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.27,0:12:17.28,English,,0,0,0,,So the next big change
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.28,0:12:21.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是这个（我们推动的）浪潮朝着我们打回来。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.28,0:12:21.64,English,,0,0,0,,that we're starting to see is kind of like that wave coming back at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.70,0:12:25.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,第一个变化仅仅是关于连接世界
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.70,0:12:25.46,English,,0,0,0,,So the first change is all about connecting the world
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.46,0:12:29.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以便拥有域名的公司能够向外发送信息
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.46,0:12:29.14,English,,0,0,0,,so that companies who have a domain could send information out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.34,0:12:34.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以提供服务到网络的边缘，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.34,0:12:34.33,English,,0,0,0,,to provide services out to the edges of their network, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.33,0:12:38.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但现在我们看到的是，网络的边缘开始回话了。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.33,0:12:38.50,English,,0,0,0,,But now what we are seeing is that the edges of the network are starting to talk back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.15,0:12:41.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,正在发生的是
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.15,0:12:41.11,English,,0,0,0,,Basically, what's happening is that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.41,0:12:47.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来自网络边缘的信息、内容和想法，正在进入并改变网络的中心
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.41,0:12:47.71,English,,0,0,0,,information and content and ideas from the edges of the network were coming in and changing the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.71,0:12:50.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，有多少人。你们能访问维基百科吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.71,0:12:50.37,English,,0,0,0,,So, how many. Can you guys get access to Wikipedia?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.88,0:12:57.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,（至于）亚马逊的商业成功，亚马逊的秘密是他们的客户。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.88,0:12:57.36,English,,0,0,0,,Amazon's business success, the secret to Amazon's business success is their customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.96,0:13:04.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是那些回过来给它们提供信息的人。亚马逊拥有关于这个世界上的书籍
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.96,0:13:04.08,English,,0,0,0,,Is the people who come back to them and give them information. Amazon has the richest collection of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.77,0:13:11.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最丰富的信息数据库，但它们并没有建立这些知识。它们从一开始所做的只不过是
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.77,0:13:11.81,English,,0,0,0,,about books in the world, but they didn't build that knowledge. What they've done is they basically they started out
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.66,0:13:16.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把信息送出去，它们在全球范围内提供这个服务。然后浪潮打了回来
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.66,0:13:16.94,English,,0,0,0,,sending information out, they are providing a service globally. And then then the wave came back
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.94,0:13:20.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是亚马逊开始收集你的知识，你的想法，你的偏好
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.94,0:13:20.70,English,,0,0,0,,and they started gathering back your knowledge, your ideas, your preferences,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.27,0:13:28.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你最喜欢的书，你对某本书的看法，对吧。这种变化就是这样发生的。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.27,0:13:28.55,English,,0,0,0,,your favorite books, your thoughts about a particular book, right? So you see how this change is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.20,0:13:33.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我相信，下一代的伟大企业，都会反映这个变化。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.20,0:13:33.96,English,,0,0,0,,The next generation of great businesses, I believe, are all going to reflect this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.70,0:13:39.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,谷歌就反映了这一点。每当你创建一个网页并
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.70,0:13:39.00,English,,0,0,0,,Google reflects this. Google reflects this by taking every time you create a web page and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.00,0:13:43.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,链接到其他网页时，你都在告诉谷歌网络上有哪些重要的内容。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.00,0:13:43.30,English,,0,0,0,,you link to other web pages, you're telling Google what's important on the web.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.64,0:13:48.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,谷歌正在有效地利用你在网络边缘产生的知识，对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.64,0:13:48.80,English,,0,0,0,,Google is effectively using your knowledge from the edge of the network, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.64,0:13:53.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，也许你还没有将所有这些企业联系起来
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.64,0:13:53.18,English,,0,0,0,,So maybe you (inaudible) connect all of those businesses and see that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.18,0:13:57.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并且发现这个潜在的效果，但它确实正在发生。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.18,0:13:57.71,English,,0,0,0,,there is an underlying effect happening there, but there really is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.71,0:13:59.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,例如，Ebay。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.71,0:13:59.39,English,,0,0,0,,Ebay. For example, ebay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.54,0:14:04.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Ebay的价值不是由Ebay创造的，是由他们所有的用户创造的。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.54,0:14:04.52,English,,0,0,0,,The value in ebay is not created by ebay, it's created by all of their users
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.52,0:14:07.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你使用Ebay，我们使用Ebay，是因为大家都在用它。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.52,0:14:07.86,English,,0,0,0,,You go to ebay, people go to ebay because everybody else is going there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.32,0:14:13.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你用维基百科，是因为其他人都在用它。你看，这些价值不是在中心创造
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.32,0:14:13.40,English,,0,0,0,,You go to Wikipedia because everybody else is going there, you see, the values not being created at the center
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.40,0:14:16.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后再输出（到网络边缘）的。这些价值是在边缘创造的，然后再赋予中心的。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.40,0:14:16.88,English,,0,0,0,,and then exported. The values are being created at the edges and then brought back in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.72,0:14:25.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我认为，这是一个非常有趣的例子，帮助我们理解边缘与中心的对话是如何发生
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.72,0:14:25.24,English,,0,0,0,,I think, it's a very interesting example of how that phenomenon of the edges talking back to the center
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.87,0:14:30.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并且正在如何改变软件世界的。对吧？在过去，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.87,0:14:30.15,English,,0,0,0,,Is changing the world of software. Right? It used to be that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.38,0:14:37.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,构建软件的最佳方式是雇用来自全世界的聪明人，并将他们转移到中心。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.38,0:14:37.02,English,,0,0,0,,the best way to build software was to hire very smart guys from all around the world and move them to the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.01,0:14:42.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，微软、甲骨文和SAP会去雇用员工
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.01,0:14:42.53,English,,0,0,0,,So Microsoft and Oracle and SAP would go and hire people
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.40,0:14:48.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并把他/她们转移到雷德蒙德（译注：微软总部）或旧金山或德国
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.40,0:14:48.47,English,,0,0,0,,and move them to Redmond or San Francisco or Germany
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.47,0:14:50.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并在那里建立集中的开发实验室。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.47,0:14:50.80,English,,0,0,0,,and they would have centralized development laboratories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.51,0:14:55.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后这些公司会把开发的成果分发给它们网络的边缘，对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.51,0:14:55.91,English,,0,0,0,,And then they would ship the results of that stuff back out to the edges of their network, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.57,0:14:59.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但在今天，自由软件正在扭转这一局面，并说，好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.57,0:14:59.33,English,,0,0,0,,But today, free software is turning that around and saying, OK,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.08,0:15:05.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让我们在网络的边缘找到对技术感兴趣的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.08,0:15:05.05,English,,0,0,0,,let's find the smartest, most self motivated people who are interested in technology
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.05,0:15:08.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最聪明、最具有动力的人。让我们利用和收集他/她们的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.05,0:15:08.72,English,,0,0,0,,at the edges of an network. Let's harness and gather all of their thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.56,0:15:15.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并把这些想法带回到中心。就这样，我们从根本上改变了软件的生产方式。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.56,0:15:15.28,English,,0,0,0,,And bring it to the center. So we completely fundamentally change the way software is being produced.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.33,0:15:24.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我认为，就像维基百科是一个比百科全书更好的知识库，比如美国世界百科全书
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.33,0:15:24.69,English,,0,0,0,,And I think, just like Wikipedia is a better repository of knowledge than say an encyclopedia like world book.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.69,0:15:28.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如大英百科全书，或者，我不知道中国的百科全书叫什么
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.69,0:15:28.99,English,,0,0,0,,or Encyclopedia Britannica, or I don't know what the equivalent Chinese is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.80,0:15:35.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但相类似的，自由软件是一个更好的技术知识库
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.80,0:15:35.48,English,,0,0,0,,So it is that free software effectively is a better repository of technology expertise.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.37,0:15:39.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比起在中心编写的专有软件而言。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.37,0:15:39.69,English,,0,0,0,,Then proprietary software, which is getting written at the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:44.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而有趣的是，自由软件实际上在维基百科之前就已经开始了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:44.96,English,,0,0,0,,So it's interesting to me that free software actually started to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.96,0:15:48.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,甚至比亚马逊的出生还要更早
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.96,0:15:48.82,English,,0,0,0,,before Wikipedia started to happen, before Amazon started to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.82,0:15:57.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还比其它一些企业更早。因为在互联网的最早期阶段，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.82,0:15:57.33,English,,0,0,0,,before some of those other businesses, because with software, in the very early days of the Internet,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.96,0:16:00.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当时使用互联网的人大部分是程序员，所以
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.96,0:16:00.87,English,,0,0,0,,The people who participated in the Internet were mostly programmers, so they
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.87,0:16:05.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他/她们最早展示出这种从网络边缘获取知识并影响中心的能力
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.87,0:16:05.32,English,,0,0,0,,started to show this ability of harnessing knowledge from the edge of the network and moving into the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.93,0:16:09.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,远远早于互联网公司
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.93,0:16:09.01,English,,0,0,0,,well before the industries did.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.04,0:16:13.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我将要向你预测，每一个行业都将被这改变。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.04,0:16:13.64,English,,0,0,0,,But I will predict to you that every single industry is going to be changed by this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.22,0:16:17.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,想想今天的音乐产业。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.22,0:16:17.06,English,,0,0,0,,Think of the music industry today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.84,0:16:21.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,今天，音乐产业看起来仍然是中心化的。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.84,0:16:21.63,English,,0,0,0,,Today, the music industry still looks like that centralized kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.63,0:16:27.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,内容在中心生产，并向我所提到的边缘输送。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.63,0:16:27.05,English,,0,0,0,,Content is produced at the center and then shipped out to the edges that I drew, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.05,0:16:30.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而十年后或十五年后将会完全是相反的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.05,0:16:30.97,English,,0,0,0,,So what's going to be what's going to be like in ten years time or fifteen year's time is the opposite
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.97,0:16:35.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,内容将在网络的边缘生产，然后输送回（中心）。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.97,0:16:35.16,English,,0,0,0,,content to be produced at the edges of the network and then shipped in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.16,0:16:39.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你将通过与你的朋友交谈来定义什么是流行音乐
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.16,0:16:39.38,English,,0,0,0,,out of that global conversation will come You will define what the popular music is by talking to your friends
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.38,0:16:44.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,通过你们的交流，从这种全球性的交流中，产生年度热门歌曲。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.38,0:16:44.70,English,,0,0,0,,and in that conversation, out of that global conversation will come the hit of the year
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.70,0:16:49.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而不是在中心定义年度热门歌曲，然后再输送给边缘。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.70,0:16:49.40,English,,0,0,0,,Rather than the hits of the year being defined at the center, and the moved out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.40,0:16:51.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有哪些行业（会受到它的影响）？工程，对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.40,0:16:51.56,English,,0,0,0,,What are the industries? Engineering. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.56,0:16:55.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有趣的是，目前人们理解自由软件运动。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.56,0:16:55.72,English,,0,0,0,,It is very interesting. At the moment, people understand the free software movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.15,0:17:02.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我认为，我们将在工程的每一个类别中都看到类似的现象出生。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.15,0:17:02.55,English,,0,0,0,,But I think we are going to see equivalent phenomenons happening in every category of engineering.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.55,0:17:07.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,机动车，让机动车设计相同的（听不清）并让每个公司都
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.55,0:17:07.97,English,,0,0,0,,Motor cars, it doesn't make sense to have motor cars design same (inaudible)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.68,0:17:13.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,重新造轮子，是不现实的。对我们来说更具有意义的是
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.68,0:17:13.04,English,,0,0,0,,and for each company to have to reinvent the wheel. it makes much more sense for us effectively
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.04,0:17:17.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让最优秀的人才来推动设计，无论这些设计在哪里产生。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.04,0:17:17.04,English,,0,0,0,,to evolve designs based on the best talent wherever it happens to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.49,0:17:23.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随着时间的推移，房子，现在有一个新的网站，能够有效地使建筑师
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.49,0:17:23.97,English,,0,0,0,,Over time, houses is now, there's now a website that's being set up, which effectively allows architects
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.17,0:17:30.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以如同编写维基百科的方式来设计房屋，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.17,0:17:30.25,English,,0,0,0,,to design houses using the same processes by which Wikipedia is written.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.90,0:17:37.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就如同自由软件被编写出来的过程，Linux操作系统被编写出来的过程
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.90,0:17:37.00,English,,0,0,0,,Using the same processes by which free software, by which Linux is written, the same processes by which
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.00,0:17:42.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也是亚马逊建立起其数据库的相同过程，利用世界各地的建筑人才
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.00,0:17:42.47,English,,0,0,0,,Amazon gathers its databases, harnessing architectural talent from all around the world 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.47,0:17:45.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来建立一个共享的建筑设计资源库。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.47,0:17:45.98,English,,0,0,0,,and producing a shared repository of architectural designs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.82,0:17:52.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我很难想到有哪个行业能够免疫这一趋势的影响。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.82,0:17:52.26,English,,0,0,0,,It's very hard for me to think of a single industry which is not going to be touched like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.01,0:17:58.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，作为一个企业家，无论你的个人爱好是什么，如果你对，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.01,0:17:58.21,English,,0,0,0,,So as an entrepreneur, whatever your personal passions are, right, if you're interested in,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.28,0:18:02.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无论你对什么感兴趣，你应该开始思考
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.28,0:18:02.16,English,,0,0,0,,whatever you're interested in, start thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.02,0:18:07.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个过程会如何影响你的行业？比如说你对化学感兴趣
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.02,0:18:07.26,English,,0,0,0,,how this process could affect your industry? if you're interested in chemistry, for example
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.26,0:18:12.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,刚好之前有位问我问题的人就是一位化学家
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.26,0:18:12.15,English,,0,0,0,,someone who was asking me questions earlier and he's a chemist
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.15,0:18:18.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你应该开始思考，你如何能从网络的边缘聚集化学知识，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.15,0:18:18.73,English,,0,0,0,,Start thinking about this. How could you aggregate chemical knowledge from the edges of the network 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.73,0:18:25.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并建立一个像维基百科一样的共享资料库？你又该如何围绕它创立一个企业？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.73,0:18:25.18,English,,0,0,0,,and build a shared repository like Wikipedia. And then how could you build a business around that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.18,0:18:29.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你该如何改变你的商业模式，去适应发生改变的运作模式？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.18,0:18:29.79,English,,0,0,0,,How do you change the business model to reflect the changed operational model?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.79,0:18:34.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为这里的每一个变化
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.79,0:18:34.16,English,,0,0,0,,Because each of these, each of these changes
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.16,0:18:39.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是由技术变革驱动的，但最终它也会成为经济变革。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.16,0:18:39.10,English,,0,0,0,,is powered by a technology change, but ultimately it's also an economic change.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.10,0:18:45.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,谷歌的商业模式与微软的商业模式就非常不同。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.10,0:18:45.14,English,,0,0,0,,And so, so, the business model of Google is very different to the business model of Microsoft.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.14,0:18:49.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,完全不同。微软真的需要去了解
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.14,0:18:49.91,English,,0,0,0,,Completely different, and Microsoft really needs to understand how
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.91,0:18:53.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们应当如何发展来跟上这些潜在的变化。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.91,0:18:53.93,English,,0,0,0,,they can evolve so that they keep up with the underlying changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.17,0:18:59.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我还想简单谈一下自由软件，作为企业家的平台
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.17,0:18:59.13,English,,0,0,0,,So I also want to talk a little bit about free software as a platform for
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.40,0:19:06.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你是一个企业家，你的工作就是要缩小差距。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.40,0:19:06.08,English,,0,0,0,,for entrepreneurs, right? If you're an entrepreneur, your job is to close a gap.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.74,0:19:15.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,缩小经济差距，找到一个机会，然后建立基础设施，为他们提供机会。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.74,0:19:15.11,English,,0,0,0,,To close an economic gap, to find an opportunity, and then build the infrastructure to service them the opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.11,0:19:20.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我们观察所有伟大的科技公司，例如NetApp，例如，这里有多少人用过VMware？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.11,0:19:20.71,English,,0,0,0,,If I look at all of the great technology businesses from NetApp, through, how many of the guys have used VMware?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.71,0:19:24.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你用过VMWare
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.71,0:19:24.75,English,,0,0,0,,so if you used VMWare, through
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.69,0:19:31.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,例如谷歌、雅虎这样的大型信息服务企业
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.69,0:19:31.77,English,,0,0,0,,the big information service businesses like Google, Yahoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.71,0:19:37.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,例如嘉信和Ebay这样的大型线上交易企业
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.71,0:19:37.29,English,,0,0,0,,big electronic trading businesses like Schwab and ebay or something
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.29,0:19:41.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有这些企业实际上都是基于自由软件所组建起来的
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.29,0:19:41.27,English,,0,0,0,,all of these businesses were actually built out using free software components.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.48,0:19:47.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,软件产业的价值不在于软件的许可成本。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.48,0:19:47.56,English,,0,0,0,,The value of the software industry is not the licensing cost of the software.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.49,0:19:54.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而是你能够使用该软件建立的经济过程的价值。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.49,0:19:54.48,English,,0,0,0,,It's the value of the economic processes that you're able to set up using that software.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.48,0:19:56.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你是一个创业者，一个今日的科技领域创业者
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.48,0:19:56.87,English,,0,0,0,,And if you're an entrepreneur, a technology entrepreneur today
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.87,0:20:01.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,值得你考虑的是，你可以使用自由软件更快地起步
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.87,0:20:01.86,English,,0,0,0,,it's worth thinking about the fact that you can get started faster, using free software.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.86,0:20:08.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你可以用自由软件更快地定制能满足你目的的工具
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.86,0:20:08.79,English,,0,0,0,,You can customize the tools to your to your purposes faster, using free software.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.79,0:20:13.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你可以用自由软件更加高效地建立起你的业务。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.79,0:20:13.34,English,,0,0,0,,You can effectively build your business much more efficiently using free software.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.34,0:20:19.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，我将自信地预测，在未来 15 到 20 年内，最好的技术企业
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.34,0:20:19.26,English,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to predict effectively that the best technology businesses over the next 15 or 20 years
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.26,0:20:26.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都会受到自由软件的助力，包括你们。以及你们用 Youtube 吗？不能？好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.26,0:20:26.33,English,,0,0,0,,are all going to be powered by free software, you too, and you guys get Youtube there? You can't? OK
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.33,0:20:28.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Youtube 是整个建立在自由软件上的。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.33,0:20:28.71,English,,0,0,0,,Youtube is all built on free software.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.71,0:20:33.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们使用 MySQL 作为数据库，用 Linux 作为核心操作系统。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.71,0:20:33.69,English,,0,0,0,,They use MySQL as a database, they use the Linux as the core operating system.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.69,0:20:39.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,YouTube 的产品是专有的，它们不给你它们的代码
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.69,0:20:39.55,English,,0,0,0,,Their offering is proprietary in the sense that they don't give you their code
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.55,0:20:44.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但所有它们用来建立业务的工具，都建立在自由软件的基础之上。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.55,0:20:44.56,English,,0,0,0,,but all of the pieces that they need to build that business are built on free software. 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.76,0:20:50.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,未来十年将是消费电子产品的时代
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.76,0:20:50.49,English,,0,0,0,,Over the next ten years is going to be consumer electronics.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.49,0:20:52.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你们有多少人知道“每个孩子一台笔记本电脑”的项目？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.49,0:20:52.80,English,,0,0,0,,How many of you guys know about the one laptop per child project?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.37,0:20:59.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的重点在于你能够以极低的价格获得正常工作的电脑
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.37,0:20:59.41,English,,0,0,0,,The thing about that is that there is functional computers at a very low price.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.09,0:21:04.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种方式完全颠覆了传统的个人电脑市场
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.09,0:21:04.94,English,,0,0,0,,It was a complete inversion of the of the traditional way of looking at the PC market
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.94,0:21:08.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,传统的看待个人电脑市场的方式是
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.94,0:21:08.67,English,,0,0,0,,the traditional way of looking at the PC market was
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.67,0:21:15.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你设一个高的价位，如 700，900，1100 美元，然后你试图在这个价位上加入
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.67,0:21:15.51,English,,0,0,0,,You set high price points like $700, $900, $1100, and then you try and squeeze as much as functionality
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.51,0:21:18.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尽你所能尽可能多的功能。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.51,0:21:18.56,English,,0,0,0,,into those price points as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.50,0:21:22.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是，通过“每个孩子一台笔记本电脑”的项目，他/她们颠覆了这一局面，他/她们说
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.50,0:21:22.78,English,,0,0,0,,But with the one laptop per child project, they turned it around, and they said,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.60,0:21:29.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上，让我们先来定义我们能提供的、有用的计算功能是多少
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.60,0:21:29.48,English,,0,0,0,,this is, actually, here, let's define a useful amount of computational functionality that we can give here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.24,0:21:33.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,接下来让我们试试看，我们能以多便宜的价格来实现这个功能。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.24,0:21:33.20,English,,0,0,0,,Let's see how cheaply we can produce that useful function.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.92,0:21:39.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,今年，我们可以用 170 美元实现，明年可能就是 130 美元，后年可能就只要 99 美元
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.92,0:21:39.94,English,,0,0,0,,This year, we can do it for $170 next year, we can do it for $130, year after that, we can do it for $99.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.94,0:21:47.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是我们就有了 100 美元以下的电脑，“一个孩子一台笔记本电脑”。我的感觉是
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.94,0:21:47.04,English,,0,0,0,,And then we've got $100 laptop, one laptop per child, and so my sense is that we're entering a time when
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.04,0:21:53.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们正在进入一个计算资源无处不在的时代。你的手机基本上就是一台电脑。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.04,0:21:53.13,English,,0,0,0,,computing is going to be absolutely ubiquitously available. Your phone is basically a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.13,0:22:01.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,摩托罗拉说，它们 60% 的手机，在三年内都将会在 Linux 上运行。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.13,0:22:01.20,English,,0,0,0,,And Motorola says that 60% of their phones, within three years, are all going to run on Linux.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.20,0:22:06.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们还不知道人们会用这些计算平台做什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.20,0:22:06.30,English,,0,0,0,,We don't yet know what people will do with those computing platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.30,0:22:11.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以我认为，多数创新、经济活动、以及下一代的大企业都将是
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.30,0:22:11.38,English,,0,0,0,,So I think that a lot of the innovation, a lot of the economic, the next generation of big businesses
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.38,0:22:17.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,手持设备或由手持设备驱动
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.38,0:22:17.31,English,,0,0,0,,are effectively going to be handheld devices or powered by handheld device
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.31,0:22:19.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而不是由事件驱动
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.31,0:22:19.36,English,,0,0,0,,rather than being powered by incidents
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.36,0:22:26.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或由PC驱动。因为有更多的人随身携带手持设备，而不是
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.36,0:22:26.60,English,,0,0,0,,or powered by the PC, because you have many, many more people who carry hand held devices than you do
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.60,0:22:29.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一直坐在电脑前。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.60,0:22:29.53,English,,0,0,0,,have people sitting in front of a computer all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.53,0:22:35.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我的笔记本电脑现在正在我的车上，但我的手机正在这里，被我随身携带。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.53,0:22:35.09,English,,0,0,0,,I've got a laptop sitting in the car right now, but I've got a phone with me right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.09,0:22:41.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，如果你能提供服务，如果你能通过某种消费类电子设备，围绕向人们提供服务
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.09,0:22:41.81,English,,0,0,0,,So if you can provide services, if you can build new economic models around delivering services to people
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.81,0:22:48.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,建立新的经济模式，那么你就有一个更大的、更有效的、可被解决的模式。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.81,0:22:48.61,English,,0,0,0,,with some sort of consumer electronic device, then you have a much bigger, effective, addressable model.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.61,0:22:54.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们一开始看到的所有围绕互联网银行、亚马逊和 ebay 等等形成的服务
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.61,0:22:54.18,English,,0,0,0,,All the service that we saw first being generated around the Internet bank, amazon and ebay, etc, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.18,0:23:03.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们都将转向并专注于消费电子产品，即小型手持设备
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.18,0:23:03.74,English,,0,0,0,,Those are all going to move towards being focused to targeted to consumer electronics, small handheld device
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.74,0:23:06.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而围绕这些设备，将会形成新一批伟大的公司
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.74,0:23:06.90,English,,0,0,0,,And there will be great businesses built around those, and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.90,0:23:11.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我希望你们中的一些人将会创立这些公司
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.90,0:23:11.33,English,,0,0,0,,I hope that some of you will be will be building those businesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.33,0:23:14.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最后说一点点 Ubuntu。你们当中有多少人熟悉 Ubuntu？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.33,0:23:14.90,English,,0,0,0,,A little bit about Ubuntu. How many of you guys are familiar with Ubuntu?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.83,0:23:18.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大约三分之一或一半。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.83,0:23:18.53,English,,0,0,0,,About a third or a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.77,0:23:23.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,（我们的）决定是让一些大的变化达成它们的自然目标
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.77,0:23:23.51,English,,0,0,0,,Decision is to take some of these big changes to their natural conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.51,0:23:30.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你看一下操作系统的许可费用，它一直在下降、下降、再下降
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.51,0:23:30.35,English,,0,0,0,,If you look at the licensing costs of operating system, It's been dropping and dropping and dropping
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.35,0:23:32.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以我们说，好吧，（这一变化的）自然结论是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.35,0:23:32.89,English,,0,0,0,,so we say, OK, what's the natural conclusion? 
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.89,0:23:35.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自然结论是，这一商业模式将会完全改变，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.89,0:23:35.43,English,,0,0,0,,The natural conclusion is that the business model completely changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.04,0:23:44.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而人们将会一同摆脱（操作系统的）许可，所以这就是为什么我们完全免费提供 Ubuntu。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.04,0:23:44.10,English,,0,0,0,,And people just get rid of licensing all together, so that's why we make Ubuntu absolutely freely available.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.10,0:23:50.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你观察正在使用的自由软件的数量，它们正在稳步增加，比如现在的苹果
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.10,0:23:50.49,English,,0,0,0,,If you look at the amount of free software that's being used. That is increasing steadily, like Apple now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.49,0:23:53.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在苹果的操作系统中大约有 80% 是自由软件
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.49,0:23:53.33,English,,0,0,0,,The Apple operating system consists of about 80% of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.33,0:23:59.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只有大约20%是专有软件。所以我们说，好吧，让我们乘上这列火车
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.33,0:23:59.21,English,,0,0,0,,is free software, and only about 20% of it is proprietary. So we say, fine, let's take that train.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.21,0:24:05.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把这列火车开到它的自然终点。因此，所有的Ubuntu都是由自由软件组成的。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.21,0:24:05.61,English,,0,0,0,,Take that train to its natural conclusion. So all of Ubuntu is made up of free software.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.61,0:24:10.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让我们确保我们建立的东西能代表
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.61,0:24:10.14,English,,0,0,0,,Let's make sure that we build something which represents the natural conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.14,0:24:12.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那些大事的自然结论。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.14,0:24:12.62,English,,0,0,0,,Of that big thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.62,0:24:16.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,正是因为这个大变化的技术，使你成为了平台。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.62,0:24:16.76,English,,0,0,0,,Because of the technology of that big change, then you become the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.76,0:24:19.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，这就是为什么我认为 Ubuntu 如此受欢迎
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.76,0:24:19.14,English,,0,0,0,,So that's why I think Ubuntu is so popular
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.14,0:24:23.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为它很好地代表了软件行业正在发生的根本性转变
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.14,0:24:23.92,English,,0,0,0,,because it best represents a fundamental shift that's going on in the software industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.92,0:24:31.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些是人们正在寻找的价值。这些是能够最有效地赋能人们的东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.92,0:24:31.48,English,,0,0,0,,That these are the values that people are looking for. These are the things which empower people most efficiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.48,0:24:35.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，作为一个企业家，如果你去创业
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.48,0:24:35.02,English,,0,0,0,,And so as an entrepreneur, if you go into entrepreneurship
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.02,0:24:38.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我会鼓励你做同样的事情，对吗？问问自己这个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.02,0:24:38.36,English,,0,0,0,,I would encourage you to do the same thing, right? Ask yourself the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.36,0:24:43.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我感兴趣的大变化是什么？这些变化将如何影响我感兴趣的领域？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.36,0:24:43.77,English,,0,0,0,,What are the big changes that I'm interested in? How will those affect the field that I'm interested in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.77,0:24:52.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以及我如何建立最能反映这种变化、最能实现这种变化的东西？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.77,0:24:52.11,English,,0,0,0,,And how do I build something which best reflects that change, which best implements that change?
